\layout Subsubsection

Conclusions on School Security Issues
\layout Standard

While the need for school security is clearly present, any proposed system
 has to meet a number of demands.
 Security levels need to be tailored to the individual school, so the system
 has to be highly flexible and configurable.
 The limitations of school funding mean that, despite recent public attention,
 school security is an issue which receives a relatively small proportion
 of overall funding.
 Therefore, the system has to be low-cost; this is the intention behind
 the use of a PC at the remote end.
 The system also has to be extendable to cover more than one entrance, ideally
 with the same method of entry.
 Again, by using a remote computer linked to multiple doors, this is a possibili
ty.
 Reliability and durability are also paramount, and the system has to be
 able to withstand abuse over a period of many years.
 Ideally, this means that all external parts should be as tough and damage-resis
tant as possible, while having a minimum number of components that could
 fail.
